<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal">Presentation by the
Licensing Officer</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">The Sub-Committee was informed that this was
an application for a variation to the current premises licence. The
applicant wished to add late night refreshments to their license
and extend the venue hours of operation to 24 hours.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal">Monday &ndash;
Sunday</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">23:00pm to 05:00am</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal">Monday &ndash;
Sunday</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">00:00am to 00:00am</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal">Condition 8</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">There shall be no sales of single cans or
bottles of beers, lagers, stout.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">And ciders from premises.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal">Condition 20</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Outside the sales of alcohol, all self-service
areas of the alcohol shall be screened off to</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Prevent access by customers and alcohol closed
signs displayed clearly.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">The Premises currently held a 24-hour license.
The condition they wished to remove related to the sale of cans of
beer and ales. Any cans of beer, alcoholic beverages, cider or
similar products were required to be sold in a minimum quantity of
four. The sale of single cans or bottles of beer, lager, stout or
cider from the premises was not permitted.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">In addition, outside the hours authorised for
the sale of alcohol, and whilst the premises were open to the
public, the licence holder was required to ensure that all alcohol
within the premises was secured behind locked grills, locked
screens or locked cabinet doors in order to prevent customer
access. This condition was proposed to be replaced with wording
referring to outside the hours for sale of alcohol. All
self-service areas of the alcohol shall be screened off to prevent
access to by customers and alcohol closed signs displayed
clearly.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">In attendance for the meeting was Mr Sharis
Kanathpathy, the agent, and Mr. Faruk Arjun. Only one
representation was submitted by the Licencing Authority relating to
the requested timings within the application. The application form
from the applicant could be found on pages 21 to 27 of the report.
Representations against the application could be found on pages 29
to 31 of the report. The statement from the applicant could be
found on pages 33 to 38 of the report and the location map and
photos of the premises were on page 39 of the report.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">The Licensing Officer informed the
Sub-Committee that:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<ul style="margin-top:0cm">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="">The Licensing Officer noted that
they did not have precise data on how many 24-hour stores were in
the borough however, they would be able to provide this information
to Committee Members outside of the meeting for more clarity.</li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="">The Licensing Officer confirmed that
the applicant was aware of the meeting that evening and that he
would have been required to attend via Microsoft Teams in order to
make his representation. The Licensing Officer confirmed that
contact with the applicant would have taken place outside the
meeting to notify him of the status of the application.</li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="">The Licensing Officer confirmed that
the applicant has had many Temporary Event Notices (TEN`s) in the
past to the early hours in the morning, and there has been no
reports of anti-social behaviour from customers or staff on the
premises.</li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
